content:
Set Article Import Parameters

Specify import parameters in a property file using key names and corresponding values. For example, use the key DateFormat to specify that a date custom field appears in the DateFormat=dd/MM/YYYY format.

REQUIRED EDITIONS AND USER PERMISSIONS
Available in: Salesforce Classic (not available in all orgs) and Lightning Experience

Salesforce Knowledge is available in Essentials and Unlimited Editions with Service Cloud. For other editions, it's available for an additional cost. Contact your Salesforce representative for more information.

USER PERMISSIONS
NEEDED
To import articles:	
Manage Salesforce Knowledge
Manage Articles
Manage Knowledge Article Import/Export
Read, Create, Edit, and Delete on the article type

KEY	DESCRIPTION	DEFAULT VALUE
DateFormat	Format of the date to read in the .csv file	yyyy-MM-dd
DateTimeFormat	Format of the date and time to read in the .csv file	yyyy-MM-dd HH:mm:ss
CSVEncoding	Character encoding used to read the .csv file	ISO8859_15_FDIS
CSVSeparator	.csv field separator	,
RTAEncoding	Default encoding used for the HTML files (if not specified in the charset attribute from the HTML meta tag)

Specify only Java date formats. Make sure that the date format is not misleading.

Save the file with the .properties extension.

EXAMPLE

DateFormat=yyyy-MM-dd
DateTimeFormat=yyyy-MM-dd HH:mm:ss
CSVEncoding=ISO8859_15_FDIS
CSVSeparator=,
RTAEncoding=UTF-8
title: Setting Up Article Import Parameters in Service Cloud
